data.enText: to make a copy of a picture, piece of text, etc.

data.chText: 未经出版者许可翻印这些习题是违法的。
data.enText: It is illegal to reproduce these worksheets without permission from the publisher.

data.chText: 这台复印机复制的色彩效果很好。
data.enText: The photocopier reproduces colours very well.

data.chText: 再生产；再制造；使再次发生；再现
data.enText: to produce sth again; to make sth happen again in the same way

data.chText: 小说的氛围在电影中得到了成功的再现。
data.enText: The atmosphere of the novel is successfully reproduced in the movie.
if people, plants, animals, etc. reproduce or reproduce themselves , they produce young

data.chText: 大多数爬行动物通过在陆地产卵进行繁殖。
data.enText: Most reptiles reproduce by laying eggs on land.
cells reproducing themselves (= making new ones)

tr: have offspring or produce more individuals of a given animal or plant
example: The Bible tells people to procreate
For the exam, you must be able to regurgitate the information

tr: make a copy or equivalent of
recreate a sound, image, idea, mood, atmosphere, etc.
example: this DVD player reproduces the sound of the piano very well
He reproduced the feeling of sadness in the portrait

value.def: If you try to reproduce something, you try to copy it.

example.ex: I shall not try to reproduce the policemen's English...
example.tran: 我不会试图去模仿那个警察讲的英语。

example.ex: The effect has proved hard to reproduce.
example.tran: 事实证明，这种效果很难再现。

value.def: If you reproduce a picture, speech, or a piece of writing, you make a photograph or printed copy of it.

example.ex: We are grateful to you for permission to reproduce this article.
example.tran: 非常感谢您允许我们复印这篇文章。

value.def: If you reproduce an action or an achievement, you repeat it.

example.ex: If we can reproduce the form we have shown in the last couple of months we will be successful.
example.tran: 如果我们能再采用前两个月的形式，我们就会成功。

value.def: When people, animals, or plants reproduce, they produce young.

example.ex: ...a society where women are defined by their ability to reproduce...
example.tran: 用生育能力衡量女性价值的社会

example.ex: We are reproducing ourselves at such a rate that our numbers threaten the ecology of the planet.
example.tran: 我们的繁衍速度太快，以至于人口数量对地球的生态系统造成了威胁。

example.ex: Genes are those tiny bits of biological information swapped in sexual reproduction.
example.tran: 基因是在有性繁殖中交换的微小生物信息。

example.ex: ...the acids which are vital for normal cell reproduction.
example.tran: 对正常细胞繁殖至关重要的酸性物质
